1. Install Python: Make sure you have Python installed on your machine. You can download the latest version of Python from the official Python website (https://www.python.org/downloads/) and follow the installation instructions for your operating system.


2. Download the Code: Download the code file containing the simulation code to your local machine. You can either copy the code from its source or download it as a file.

3. Open a command prompt or terminal and navigate to the folder where the code was downloaded
  ```
 cd path/to/file
  ```
  
4.   Install Required Libraries: run the following command to install the required libraries:
   ```
  pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

5. Run the Application: Run the following command to start the Streamlit application:
   ```
   streamlit run model_v3.py
   ```
